@hls@n displays contents of the current directory

@eSYNTAX:
@p$@n ls @p[pattern]

@eEXAMPLES:
@p$@n ls
  @hlists all files in the current directory

@p$@n ls *.sh
  @hlists all shell scripts in the current directory

@p$@n ls dirname
  @hlists the files in the given subdirectory (can be multiple levels deep if you separate the directory names with slashes)
